data-triple-N3.o: "Leicester City Football Club, also known as The Foxes, is an English professional football club based at the King Power Stadium (previously called the Walkers Stadium) in Leicester. They currently play in the Football League Championship, having been promoted as champions from Football League One in the 2008–09 season. The club was founded in 1884 as Leicester Fosse, playing on a field near Fosse Road."@en
